# Data Feeds, Track API & Chart Views

The user wants to transition the app from a static local prototype to a system that can distribute a "Current Track" via an API request, collect data from multiple users, and display independent chart views (including a word cloud).

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> To support an API request to set the track and to collect word cloud texts from multiple users simultaneously, we should introduce a lightweight Node.js backend. We can use Express and Server-Sent Events (SSE) to push track updates to the audience. This replaces the `python -m http.server` approach. Please confirm if adding a Node.js server is acceptable.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend & API (`server.js`)
We will create a simple Node.js/Express server to:
- Serve the static files ([index.html](file:///d:/dev/chadmairn/concert-app/index.html), [styles.css](file:///d:/dev/chadmairn/concert-app/styles.css), [script.js](file:///d:/dev/chadmairn/concert-app/script.js), etc.).
- Expose a `POST /api/track` endpoint to set the current track by ID or title.
- Expose a SSE endpoint `/api/stream` so clients automatically update their UI when the track changes.
- Expose a `POST /api/events` endpoint to collect data feeds (moods, colors, reactions, texts).
- Expose a `GET /api/events` endpoint to serve data to the chart pages.

### Configuration updates ([config.yaml](file:///d:/dev/chadmairn/concert-app/config.yaml))
- Add a `tracks` list to [config.yaml](file:///d:/dev/chadmairn/concert-app/config.yaml).
- Each track will have `id`, `title`, `artist`, and `color`.

### UI Updates ([index.html](file:///d:/dev/chadmairn/concert-app/index.html), [styles.css](file:///d:/dev/chadmairn/concert-app/styles.css), [script.js](file:///d:/dev/chadmairn/concert-app/script.js))
- **Track Banner**: Add a banner at the top of the app shell displaying the current track.
- **Text Prompt**: Modify the "Optional Note" area to prompt for text associated with the current track (for the word cloud).
- **Reaction Slider**: Replace the "Like / Dislike" buttons with a slider (values: "Meh", "Like", "Applause"). Ensure this fires a specific event when changed.
- **Remove Extras & Inline Charts**: Remove the "Extras" section. Replace the inline charts area at the bottom with large buttons/links navigating to the chart views.

### Chart Views
We will create dedicated HTML pages (or a routing mechanism) for the charts:
- `charts-all.html`: A dashboard showing all 3 charts (Mood, Color, Reaction) and the Word Cloud.
- `chart-mood.html`: Full-screen Mood chart.
- `chart-color.html`: Full-screen Color chart.
- `chart-reaction.html`: Full-screen Reaction chart.
- `chart-words.html`: Full-screen Word Cloud (using a library like `wordcloud2.js` or similar).

## Verification Plan
1. Start the Node.js server.
2. Open the app in multiple browser tabs simulating different users.
3. Make an API request (e.g., via `curl`) to set the current track. Verify the banner updates in all open tabs instantly.
4. Test the slider, color, mood, and word cloud inputs.
5. Open the data views and ensure they pull from the aggregated Node.js memory/data store and render correctly.
